<TITLE> Govt buying 3 dredgers after gap of 35 years </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 1 (bdnews24.com)  The government is set to purchase three dredgers, the first in over three decades, for critical maintenance of river navigability, shipping minister Shajahan Khan told parliament on Monday. To a question by Comilla-8 MP Nasimul Alam Chowdhury, he said the government is procuring three dredgers "soon". Another 17 dredgers will be procured by 2015, he added. They will be the first dredgers to be purchased in 35 years, the minister said. Khan also said the government would procure four sea trucks and a 500-passenger ship for BIWTC (Bangladesh Inland Water Transport Corporation). The government will also auction off two vessels of the inland transport authority and two of Bangladesh Shipping Corporation "The government has decided in principle to sell two BIWTA (Bangladesh Inland Water Transport Authority) inspection vessels  Sonartori and Sonarkheya  through auction," the minister said in reply to a question by Pirojpur-3 constituency MP Anwar Hossain. Answering another question by Brahmanbaria-4 MP Md Shah Alam, he said two ships  MV Banglar Gourab and MV Banglar Urmi  under state-run BSC would be sold as they are no longer viable to operate. The minister said tender have also been floated to auction off two ships and four pontoons of Mongla Port Authority.
